The '''Scottish Handball Association''' is the governing body for non-[[International Handball Federation]] related matters of [[team handball]] in [[Scotland]] while the [[British Handball Association]] has governance over matters relating to the [[International Handball Federation]]. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://britishhandball.worldhandball.com/DesktopDefault.aspx?menuid=1761|title=Responsibilities of Associations|publisher=[[European Handball Federation]]|accessdate=2009-04-18}}</ref>   <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eurohandball.com/federations/gbr/Great+Britain|title=National Federation / GBR (for IHF Matters only)|publisher=[[European Handball Federation]]|accessdate=2009-04-18}}</ref> The SHA is a member of the [[European Handball Federation]] (EHF).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eurohandball.com/federations/sco/Scotland|title=EHF Member Federation / SCO|publisher=[[European Handball Federation]]|accessdate=2009-03-08}}</ref>

